   "source": [
    "# Core imports\n",
    "import dcgpy\n",
    "import pygmo as pg\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "# Sympy is nice to have for basic symbolic manipulation.\n",
    "from sympy import init_printing\n",
    "from sympy.parsing.sympy_parser import *\n",
    "init_printing()\n",
    "# Plotting\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "# Pickling\n",
    "import pickle as pk"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 43,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load the data\n",
    "with open(\"data.pk\", \"rb\") as f:\n",
    "    Xs,Ys  = pk.load(f)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 44,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/latex": [
       "$\\displaystyle \\left( 0.26, \\  0.34\\right)$"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "(0.26, 0.34)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 44,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 612x720 with 12 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Visualize them\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows = 4, ncols=3, sharex=True, sharey=True, figsize=(8.5,10))\n",
    "for i, ax in enumerate(np.reshape(axes,(12))[:12]):\n",
    "    ax.scatter(Xs[i], Ys[i], s=2.0, alpha=0.5)\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0, 1.5)\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(0.26, 0.34)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# We define our kernel set, that is the mathematical operators we will\n",
    "# want our final model to possibly contain. \n",
    "ss = dcgpy.kernel_set_double([\"sum\", \"diff\", \"mul\", \"div\", \"exp\"])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 45,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\tData dimension (points): 1\n",
      "\tData dimension (labels): 1\n",
      "\tData size: 1440\n",
      "\tKernels: [sum, diff, mul, div, exp]\n",
      "\tLoss: MSE\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Instantiate the symbolic regression optimization problem\n",
    "# Note: we allow for three constants in the final expression\n",
    "X = np.reshape(Xs[0], (len(Xs[0]),1))\n",
    "Y = np.reshape(Ys[0], (len(Ys[0]),1))\n",
    "udp = dcgpy.symbolic_regression(points = X, labels = Y, kernels=ss(), n_eph=3, rows =1, cols=16, levels_back=8, multi_objective=False)\n",
    "print(udp)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 46,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# We instantiate here the evolutionary strategy we want to use to search for models.\n",
    "# In this case we use a single objective memetic algorithm.\n",
    "uda  = dcgpy.mes4cgp(gen = 2000, max_mut = 15)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# The evolution will happen in parallel using an archipelago with no connections\n",
    "archi = pg.archipelago(algo = uda, prob = udp, n = 8, pop_size=4)\n",
    "archi.evolve(5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[array([2.53676988e-05]),\n",
       " array([2.38481619e-05]),\n",
       " array([2.38109105e-05]),\n",
       " array([2.49418679e-05]),\n",
       " array([2.38471303e-05]),\n",
       " array([2.4257763e-05]),\n",
       " array([2.40675458e-05]),\n",
       " array([5.92793339e-05])]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 27,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "archi.wait()\n",
    "with open(\"results.pk\", \"wb\") as file:\n",
    "    pk.dump((archi), file)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },

       "                       2          2     \n",
       "                     x  + x   x      "
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 39,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Lets have a look to the symbolic representation of our model (using sympy)\n",
    "best = archi.get_champions_x()[2]\n",
    "parse_expr(udp.prettier(best))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# And lets see what our model actually predicts on the inputs\n",
    "Y_pred = udp.predict(X, best)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 41,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

   ],
   "source": [
